      <section eId="sec_CHC-1559">
        <num>CHC 1559</num>
        <heading>1559. Â Surrender of parental rights to a terminally ill child</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1559__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A parent or guardian who refuses to consent to the medical care and treatment of his child as required by this Chapter may at any time execute a voluntary act of surrender pursuant to Title XI and place the child in the legal custody of the department or a licensed adoption agency.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1559__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The department or agency shall immediately provide the treatment necessary for the child and shall make every effort to find an adoptive home for the child.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=73017</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
